Fork the repository from the GitHub repository link.
Clone the forked repository to your local machine: git clone https://github.com/your-username/automated-code-review.git.
Create a new branch to implement your changes: git checkout -b feature/new-feature.
Make the necessary improvements and additions to the algorithm and its features. Consider the following enhancements:
Integration with popular code editors and IDEs to provide real-time feedback during development.
Support for multiple programming languages by extending the algorithm's capabilities.
Development of a user-friendly web interface for easier code submission and review.
Implementation of machine learning techniques to improve code review accuracy and provide more personalized recommendations.
Configure the code analysis library based on your project's coding style guidelines and preferences.
Thoroughly test the algorithm on a variety of code samples to verify its accuracy and effectiveness.
Commit your changes with descriptive commit messages: git commit -m "Add new feature: code complexity analysis".
Push your changes to your forked repository: git push origin feature/new-feature.
Create a new pull request on the original repository to submit your changes for review and inclusion.
